    "body": "I am not sure what the test is intended for but I can tell for sure pure sol function return L2 block height(number), transaction return L1 block height(but this seems to be the last 'sync' one, not when it is actually executed on L1). \r\n\r\nI can understand why pure function may not be the same(this is even true on ethereum as when the transaction is included is unknown). It is the unpredictable block# for transaction that is the issue. there is no 'time' anymore. ethereum may not have an 'accurate time' but a reasonably correct ballpark. optimism has none\r\n",
